<!--   <!-\- </p> -\-> -->

<!--   <!-\- <p> -\-> -->
<!--   <!-\-   As Calculus developed from the ideas of Leibniz and Newton -\-> -->
<!--   <!-\-   into the powerful tool is has become, the integral notation -\-> -->
<!--   <!-\-   evolved from Leibniz<rsq/> simple <q>S</q> (for -\-> -->
<!--   <!-\-   <foreign>summa</foreign> or <q>sum</q>) into a sophisticated -\-> -->
<!--   <!-\-   and rather esoteric bit of notation.         Our purpose in -\-> -->
<!--   <!-\-   this section is to introduce and explain that evolution.  It -\-> -->
<!--   <!-\-   will take time, -\-> -->
<!--   <!-\-   effort, and a lot of practice to get comfortable with it. Be -\-> -->
<!--   <!-\-   patient with yourself. -\-> -->
<!--   <!-\- </p> -\-> -->


