<!--   computation will bring us back to our old problem of computing -->
<!--   antiderivatives. For now, let's just focus on computation of -->
<!--   definite integrals via the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus. With -->
<!--   the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus in mind, we introduce the -->
<!--   following notation. If <m>\dfdx{A}{x}=y</m> then -->
<!--   <me>\int_{x=a}^by\dx{x}=\int_{x=a}^by\dx{x}=\left.A(x)\right|_{x=a}^b{}=A(b)-A(a)</me> -->
<!--   The symbol <m>\left.A(x)\right|_{x=a}^b</m> is read aloud as -->
<!--   <q><m>A</m> of <m>x</m> evaluated from <m>x=a</m> to -->
